Hello all,

I am attempting to implement the Single Send API to send transactional emails for a client.

In order to test, I’m using Postman.


Steps I’ve done:

Created a Private App that I named “Email Single Send API” and added the transactional-email scope.

I created an email using a regular template, added some content including some personalization tokens as follows:


&lt;p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 125%;"&gt;Hi, {{ contact.firstName }};&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Web Order Number: &lt;a href="{{ custom.orderLink }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;{{ custom.webOrderNumber }}&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;Sales Order Number: {{ custom.salesOrderNumber }}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Payment Method: &lt;span style="font-weight: bold;"&gt;{{ custom.paymentMethod }}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;PO Number: &lt;span style="font-weight: bold;"&gt;{{ custom.poNumber }}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


In postman I setup a new HTTP request with

- POST type to <https://api.hubapi.com/marketing/v4/email/single-send>

- Bearer token using the token from the private app mentioned above

- The following JSON for the body:


{

"emailId": "155777167166",

"message": {

"to": "<mailto:rebecca.bretzinger@neweratech.com|rebecca.bretzinger@neweratech.com>"

},

"contactProperties": {

"firstName": "Rebecca"

},

"customProperties": {

"orderMethod": "PO Order",

"poNumber": "1234",

"webOrderNumber": "5678",

"salesOrderNumber": "4321",

"orderLink": "<https://www.google.com>"

}

}


The response is
{

"status": "error",

"message": "unauthorized request",

"correlationId": "3e25922e-ba35-45ff-8441-09516f6cad1d"

}

Should I add any additional scopes to the private app? The transactional-email was the only one mentioned in the Single Send API documentation page.

Something else?

Thanks to anyone who can provide insight!
